The paper deals with the analysis of the restricted isometry property (RIP) of a matrix type, which is relevant in many linear inverse problems. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and bounds, which are common in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the matrix type in sparse signal recovery and tensor decomposition problems, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
